CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 30, 1941, pg. 9, reads: "The Kiddies at the Smoketowners...New York Visitors...Grandfathers Enjoy Day in Woods - Photographer Harris snapped these photos last week-end. The attractive children on the automobile are Marcia Nickens, Jimmie Henry, Garfield Nickens, Jr., Joyce Robinson.  Second row, Bob Grant Jr., Jimmy Jackson, Sylvia King, Jenine Henry, William Robinson, Jackie Jackson and Buddie Williams.  The girl on the end is the Ed Thompson's daughter.  They were present with their parents at The Smoketowner's picnic..."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of girls and boys gathered around car, including Marcia Nickens, Jimmie Henry, Garfield Nickens Jr., Robinson, Grant Jr., Jimmy Jackson, King, Jenine Henry, William "Buzz" Robinson, Jack "Jackie" Jackson, Buddie Williams, and Thompson, gathered for Smoketowners picnic
